        "Data": [
          "<h1>Applies to</h1>\r\n  <ul>\r\n    <li>PHP</li>\r\n  </ul>\r\n  <h1>What to Do</h1>\r\n  <p>Configure PHP to make sessions time-out after a certain period of time, even if the user is active.</p>\r\n  <h1>Why</h1>\r\n  <p>Limiting session life-time makes it harder to hijack sessions.</p>\r\n  <h1>How</h1>\r\n  <p>To set an absolute session time limit, configure the <em>php.ini</em> file to include the following directive:</p>\r\n  <pre>session.cookie_lifetime = 60000</pre>\r\n  <p>The snippet above sets the maximum session life-time to 60000 seconds by limiting the life-time of the session cookies.</p>"
